2nd Hop Harvest release, classic cascade grown locally with Ryefield Hops from Bega Valley NSW. 

Cascade’s zesty pine and grapefruit notes shine with a clean malt bill. With unique herbal and earthy flavours, a signature of wet hops.

beer.beer_style: Pale Ale - New England / Hazy
beer.beer_description: A juicy, fruity pale ale with a smooth body expressing the tropical notes of the Strata & Idaho 7.

beer.beer_style: IPA - Imperial / Double Black
beer.beer_description: Fruited beer that’s not sour! A bucket load of Mulberries and then some more added to this beer giving a good balance of sweet and tart flavours with a hint of woody cedar to bridge the piney bitterness an of an American classic.

beer.beer_style: Bitter - Extra Special / Strong (ESB)
beer.beer_description: Floral and earthy aromas accompany fruit esters showcased by the characterful British yeast pitched on this ESB. The lower carbonation illuminates the biscuity, nutty, caramel flavours of this beer. The finish strikes a delightful balance of malty sweetness and bitterness, perfect for the cooling months ahead.

beer.beer_style: IPA - American
beer.beer_description: A juicy, fruity pale ale with a smooth body expressing the tropical notes of the Strata & Idaho 7.

beer.beer_style: Cream Ale
beer.beer_description: A cream ale inspired from post-Prohibition, including corn in the grist. Offering subtle but restrained flavours of the Kölsch yeast. Light & crispy with a clean mouthfeel. A classic lawnmower beer, suitable for all occasions.

beer.beer_style: IPA - New England / Hazy
beer.beer_description:
Floating aromas of mango, papaya and pear lift from the glass. The hefty combination of rolled oats, malted wheat and golden naked oats provides the silky mouthfeel.

The Cloud chaser brings a local twist on the Hazy IPA, bringing together the best of Australian and US hop varieties.

Chase the little moments of delight in the day with this glowing Hazy IPA.

beer.beer_style: IPA - Imperial / Double New England / Hazy
beer.beer_description:
A passport to a sensory adventure that embodies the energy of a tropical paradise strip, featuring NZ Superdelic Hops.

Aromas of bright neon red candy give way to lush explosions of tropical / mango that dance on your palate.

The hazy, pillowy texture of this IPA wraps around your senses like a tropical daydream.

beer.beer_style: IPA - New England / Hazy
beer.beer_description:
Juicy, Tropical, Citrus Aromas lift from a thick white head.

The flavour of the Citrus & berries is supported by a medium-full-bodied mouthfeel with a sweet-mid honey finish.

beer.beer_style: Pale Ale - XPA (Extra Pale)
beer.beer_description: Hop forward, with a balanced clean finish. Showcasing the fruit and floral aromas and flavours of the best Aussie hops.

beer.beer_style: Pale Ale - Other
Stout - Irish Dry
beer.beer_description: Aromas of roasted Ethiopian coffee and dark chocolate lift from a thick, tight head. A silky blend of light caramel & biscuit flavours, offset with the herbaceous bitterness from UK Fuggles. The finish is smooth, dry & clean with lingering notes of coffee.

beer.beer_style: IPA - Imperial / Double New England / Hazy
IPA - Red
beer.beer_description:
Double dry hopped with Mosaic and Cascade yielding bold clean aromas of citrus and stone fruits.

A solid malt back bone of English an Australian malts provides a mellow balance of light caramel and toffee to the dank, piney hop profile.

Inspired by the feel of the breweries red iron cladding, this beer feels like home.

beer.beer_style: Pale Ale - Other
beer.beer_description: Wet Hopped Pale Ale

beer.beer_style: IPA - American
beer.beer_description:
A mid strength alternative with an upfront bold citrus hop character. 

The classic fruity ale esters and cleansing peppery, dry finish add to the drinkability.

beer.beer_style: Sour - Fruited
beer.beer_description: A pale, refreshing sour beer with a clean lactic sourness. A gentle, pale malt flavour supports the lemony sourness with moderate fruity peach esters.

beer.beer_style: Red Ale - Irish
beer.beer_description: This balanced Nitro beer, highlights roughly 7 different malts and a healthy does of roasted barley, which gives the beer its rich colour. Featuring an approachable hop bitterness which rests on the palate, a candy-like caramel malt sweetness, slight toffee notes lingers.

beer.beer_style: Märzen
beer.beer_description:
Quality German malts lends to a clean,
toasty, bread crust malt flavour.
marzen is soft, elegant, and nuanced,
with a rich malty aftertaste.
Expect visions of stein filled tents with each sip.

beer.beer_style: IPA - Cold
beer.beer_description:
Wester than West Coast! - This IPA variant showcases bright citrus-fruit hoppiness but with a cleaner finish  This is thanks to the inclusion of rolled rice and flaked corn in the grist, the fermentation regime, and multiple modern hop additions.

It sure as heck isn't "just an IPL" as naysayers have accused, but certainly is an esky filler.

beer.beer_style: IPA - New England / Hazy
beer.beer_description:
Lazy Haze brings depth of flavour without sacrificing the laid back times you seek

Galaxy hops unleash a wave of passion fruit while the citra gives lively kick of lime

Let your taste buds enjoy the amplified taste without compromising the chill factor

beer.beer_style: Lager - IPL (India Pale Lager)
beer.beer_description:
Bolder in character, this IPL is a firm exhibit of fresh Simcoe with weeks of cold conditioning that form a delicately balanced
and clean ester profile. Don't underestimate his force.
